{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"PeriodicSyncEvent","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Periodic_Background_Synchronization_API\">Web Periodic Background Synchronization API</a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Interfaces</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent\"><code>PeriodicSyncEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager\"><code>PeriodicSyncManager</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerRegistration/periodicSync\"><code>ServiceWorkerRegistration.periodicSync</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/onperiodicsync\"><code>ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.onperiodicsync</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/periodicsync_event\"><code>ServiceWorkerGlobalScope</code>: <code>periodicsync</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>PeriodicSyncEvent</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Periodic_Background_Synchronization_API\"><code>Web Periodic Background Synchronization API</code></a> provides a way to run tasks in the service worker with network connectivity.</p>\n<p>An instance of this event is passed to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/periodicsync_event\" title=\"periodicsync\"><code>periodicsync</code></a> handler. This happens periodically, at an interval greater than or equal to that set in the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncManager/register\"><code>PeriodicSyncManager.register()</code></a> method. Other implementation-specific factors such as the user's engagement with the site decide the actual interval.</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"75\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"37.5\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      Event\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"75\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"105\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" \"=\"\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"75,14 85,9 85,19 75,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ExtendableEvent\">\n    <rect x=\"105\" y=\"0\" width=\"120\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"165\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      ExtendableEvent\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"225\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"255\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" \"=\"\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"225,14 235,9 235,19 225,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"255\" y=\"0\" width=\"136\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"323\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      PeriodicSyncEvent\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"constructor","title":"Constructor","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"periodicsyncevent.periodicsyncevent\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent/PeriodicSyncEvent\"><code>PeriodicSyncEvent.PeriodicSyncEvent()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Creates a new <code>PeriodicSyncEvent</code> object. This constructor is not typically used. The browser creates these objects itself and provides them to <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ServiceWorkerGlobalScope/periodicsync_event\" title=\"onperiodicsync\"><code>onperiodicsync</code></a> callback.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"properties","title":"Properties","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"periodicsyncevent.tag\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent/tag\"><code>PeriodicSyncEvent.tag</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the developer-defined identifier for this <code>PeriodicSyncEvent</code>. Multiple tags can be used by the web app to run different periodic tasks at different frequencies.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"methods","title":"Methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Inherits methods from its parent <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ExtendableEvent\"><code>ExtendableEvent</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>The following example shows how to respond to a periodic sync event in the service worker.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code>self<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'periodicsync'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token parameter\">event</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>event<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>tag <span class=\"token operator\">==</span> <span class=\"token string\">'get-latest-news'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    event<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">waitUntil</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token function\">fetchAndCacheLatestNews</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>fetchAndCacheLatestNews</code> is a developer defined function.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/periodic-background-sync/#periodicsync-event","title":"Web Periodic Background Synchronization"}],"query":"api.PeriodicSyncEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.PeriodicSyncEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://web.dev/periodic-background-sync/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Richer offline experiences with the Periodic Background Sync API</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://webplatformapis.com/periodic_sync/periodicSync_improved.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">A Periodic Background Sync demo app</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Constructor","id":"constructor"},{"text":"Properties","id":"properties"},{"text":"Methods","id":"methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The PeriodicSyncEvent interface of the Web Periodic Background Synchronization API provides a way to run tasks in the service worker with network connectivity.","popularity":0.0007,"modified":"2022-03-28T08:49:26.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/periodicsyncevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/periodicsyncevent/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/0f418ddb7c73511ccdc85db22d986d12d4b31f7a","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/PeriodicSyncEvent","title":"PeriodicSyncEvent"}],"pageTitle":"PeriodicSyncEvent - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}